      <h3>Why Olly Sleep Is the Best Melatonin Gummy Overall</h3>

      <p>Olly has earned its position at the top of the melatonin gummy market by executing a deceptively simple strategy: combine clinically supported ingredients at effective doses, make the product genuinely enjoyable to take, and price it competitively. Their Sleep gummies deliver 3mg of melatonin per two-gummy serving alongside 100mg of L-Theanine and a proprietary blend of chamomile, passionflower, and lemon balm extracts. This multi-ingredient approach is not just marketing — it addresses sleep through complementary mechanisms. Melatonin signals your circadian clock that it is time to sleep, L-Theanine reduces mental agitation by promoting alpha brain wave activity, and the botanical blend calms the nervous system through GABAergic pathways.</p>

      <p>In our four-week testing panel, Olly Sleep produced consistent drowsiness within 20 to 30 minutes of ingestion. Testers reported falling asleep an average of 15 minutes faster than baseline, with notably fewer instances of the "racing mind" that prevents sleep onset. The blackberry zen flavor was rated 9.2 out of 10 for taste — the highest score among all products we tested — and the soft, non-sticky texture made nightly compliance effortless.</p>

      <p>The one legitimate consideration is dosage sensitivity. If you are new to melatonin or know from experience that you are sensitive to it, 3mg may produce vivid dreams or slight morning grogginess. In that case, start with a single gummy (1.5mg) rather than the two-gummy serving. For the vast majority of users, however, Olly Sleep represents the best overall combination of efficacy, taste, ingredient quality, and value in the melatonin gummy category.</p>

