      <h3>Nature Made: The Gold Standard in Melatonin Purity</h3>

      <p>If your primary concern is knowing exactly what is in the bottle — and nothing else — Nature Made holds a certification that no amount of marketing can replicate: <strong>USP Verification</strong>. The United States Pharmacopeia is an independent, nonprofit scientific organization that tests supplements to verify label accuracy, dissolution rates, and absence of harmful contaminants. A 2023 study in the Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine found that <strong>nearly 25% of melatonin supplements contained significantly more or less melatonin than their labels stated</strong>, with some products containing up to 478% of the labeled dose. USP Verification eliminates this uncertainty entirely.</p>

      <p>Nature Made's formula is deliberately simple: 3mg of melatonin per two-gummy serving with no added botanicals, amino acids, or proprietary blends. For consumers who want pharmaceutical-grade melatonin without the variability introduced by complex multi-ingredient formulas, this simplicity is a feature, not a limitation. You know precisely what you are ingesting, and independent verification confirms it.</p>

      <p>The trade-off is the experience. Nature Made gummies are adequate in taste and texture, but they lack the treat-like quality of Olly or SugarBear products. For people who value verification and purity above all else — particularly those taking melatonin alongside prescription medications where ingredient certainty matters — Nature Made is the clear choice in this category.</p>

