      <h3>ZzzQuil Pure Zzzs: The Research-Aligned Low-Dose Option</h3>

      <p>ZzzQuil has been a household name in sleep aids for decades, and their Pure Zzzs line represents a deliberate shift toward cleaner, supplement-grade formulations. The standout feature is the low melatonin dose — just 1 to 2mg per serving. This range aligns closely with what Dr. Richard Wurtman's landmark MIT research identified as the optimal supplemental melatonin dose. While most competitors default to 3mg or higher, ZzzQuil designed their product around the principle that physiological doses are more effective than pharmacological ones for the majority of healthy adults.</p>

      <p>The formula also includes lavender, chamomile, lemon balm, and valerian root. Each of these botanicals has a historical basis for promoting relaxation, and while the clinical evidence varies in strength, the combination creates a noticeable calming effect that our testers reported appreciating. The wildberry vanilla flavor is subtle rather than overpowering, and the gummy texture is among the softest in this category.</p>

      <p>The primary limitation is dosing consistency. Because the melatonin content per gummy is low, manufacturing tolerances mean one gummy might deliver 0.8mg while another delivers 1.3mg. This variance is not dangerous, but it means your experience can shift slightly from night to night. For users who prioritize absolute consistency, the higher-dosed products like Olly or Nature Made offer more predictable delivery. For those who want a low-dose, botanically enhanced melatonin gummy from a brand with decades of consumer trust, ZzzQuil Pure Zzzs is an excellent choice.</p>

