      <h3>Natrol Melatonin: The 90-Day Budget Champion</h3>

      <p>If your priority is straightforward melatonin supplementation at the lowest possible cost, Natrol is the undisputed value leader. At <strong>$0.11 per serving with 90 servings per bottle</strong>, you are looking at a full three-month supply for under $10. No other melatonin gummy in this ranking comes close to that per-serving cost. Natrol earned its position as the number-one selling melatonin brand in America through decades of consistent quality at accessible prices, and their gummies maintain the same manufacturing standards that built that reputation.</p>

      <p>The formula is deliberately stripped down to its essential component: 5mg of melatonin per serving with no additional botanicals, amino acids, or proprietary blends. For people who respond well to melatonin alone and do not need L-Theanine, chamomile, or other supporting ingredients, this simplicity is an advantage. You know exactly what you are getting, and the third-party testing confirms that the label matches the contents.</p>

      <p>The caveat, however, is significant. The 5mg dose is <strong>higher than what most sleep researchers recommend</strong> as a starting point. The MIT study on optimal melatonin dosing found that 0.3mg was sufficient to restore normal nighttime melatonin levels, and that supraphysiological doses above 3mg did not improve sleep onset further while increasing the likelihood of vivid dreams and next-morning grogginess. If you choose Natrol, consider taking one gummy (2.5mg) instead of the recommended two-gummy serving until you know how you respond.</p>

